MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CRITICAL (blocked first deploy):
- kubernetes/services/*.yaml had literal REPLACE_ACR_LOGIN_SERVER in image:
  fields. Switched to ${ACR_LOGIN_SERVER} plus scripts/render-k8s-manifests.sh.
- No admin bootstrap path. Added INITIAL_ADMIN_EMAIL promotion in user-service.
- Terraform backend assumed pre-existing rg/storage. Added terraform/bootstrap/.

OTHER FIXES:
- Aligned raw K8s secret names with Helm (per-service *-kv-secrets).
- Updated README diagram: NGINX entry, not Azure App Gateway.
- terraform/modules/aks: replaced literal prevent_destroy=true with a
  variable-driven Azure management lock (enable_destroy_protection).
- task-service Service Bus singleton now resets on send failure.
- Lazy bcrypt dummy hash (no module-import cost).
- DB pool sizes are settings-driven; docker-compose uses smaller pools.
- Removed XFF check on /metrics; rely on NetworkPolicy.
- ALLOWED_ORIGINS accepts comma-separated and JSON forms.
- Wired ALLOWED_ORIGINS/RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS/AUTH_RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS/REDIS_URL
  into api-gateway K8s/Helm.
- imagePullPolicy: Always -> IfNotPresent in raw manifests.
- Removed personal commit_9fixes.ps1 / push_to_github.ps1; gitignored *.ps1.
- README Quick Start is now end-to-end runnable.

TEST FIXES (pre-existing test bugs caught while iterating):
- test_correlation.py: missing Request type annotation.
- test_proxy_headers.py: 2-tuple unpack of a 3-tuple return.
- task-service test_schemas.py: HTML-only inputs need self-closing tags.
- notification-service test_consumer.py: 'or' -> stronger CR/LF guarantee.

All 214 unit tests pass.
